caption_original:
Why study animal guts? Because their microbial communities play a role in digestion. By learning more about how microbes assist in digestion, scientists could improve farm animals’ ability to digest food and grow faster and stronger.

Because of the importance of digestion to growth, AAFC researchers are involved with several projects related to the microbiota in the guts of animals. Two are particularly interesting, because they focus on the guts of animals you might not think have much to do with agriculture: beavers and pandas. http://ow.ly/hsQV30gBbvw

By learning more about how microbes assist in digestion, scientists could improve farm animals’ ability to digest food and grow faster and stronger. Two are particularly interesting, because they focus on the guts of animals you might not think have much to do with agriculture: beavers and pandas.
